DataSpace bitstream GET requests (view/download requests) respond with a warning for certain Items

comments.body: https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/pull/3873/files did not resolve this issue, I am still struggling to diagnose this, and shall proceed with this as an urgent priority.

I have been able to isolate the bitstreams for this Item with the following:

```bash
dataspace_prod_db=> select bit.bitstream_id,bit.internal_id from bitstream as bit inner join bundle2bitstream as b2b on bit.bitstream_id=b2b.bitstream_id inner join bundle as bun on bun.bundle_id=b2b.bundle_id inner join item2bundle as i2b on bun.bundle_id=i2b.bundle_id where i2b.item_id=28854;
 bitstream_id |               internal_id
--------------+-----------------------------------------
        39149 | 123303021729412055520366204091862923761
       137193 | 29176517213505381792192318745048114491
(2 rows)
```

This is the affected file, I am not quite certain why this is proving to be problematic:

```bash
dspace@gcp-dataspace-prod1:~$ file /mnt/disks/dataspaceproddatastore/prod-copy/assetstore_production/29/17/65/29176517213505381792192318745048114491
/mnt/disks/dataspaceproddatastore/prod-copy/assetstore_production/29/17/65/29176517213505381792192318745048114491: PDF document, version 1.4
dspace@gcp-dataspace-prod1:~$ stat /mnt/disks/dataspaceproddatastore/prod-copy/assetstore_production/29/17/65/29176517213505381792192318745048114491
  File: /mnt/disks/dataspaceproddatastore/prod-copy/assetstore_production/29/17/65/29176517213505381792192318745048114491
  Size: 61220117        Blocks: 119576     IO Block: 4096   regular file
Device: 810h/2064d      Inode: 51511900    Links: 1
Access: (0664/-rw-rw-r--)  Uid: ( 1005/  dspace)   Gid: ( 1005/  dspace)
Access: 2023-05-09 09:40:33.332799458 -0400
Modify: 2019-08-27 08:46:55.665441000 -0400
Change: 2021-09-20 15:43:28.020223109 -0400
 Birth: -
```

Observing the URL structure, it may be the case that this is actually related to some inconsistency in resolving bitstream file names to bitstream binaries during requests for downloads. Please note that, during download attempts, `%2c_` is encoded into `,_`:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/0e770501-46f9-4ce6-b520-18b159e32d04)

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/3e6dc734-8205-4fd3-ac0a-ee3c71790cb2)
